<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="579" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1435,1714]" pageId="2" pageNumber="579">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,1435,1461]" pageId="2" pageNumber="579">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Body length 10.0–16.0 mm. Mystax white. Ocellar and postocular setae white. Scutum silvery tomentose with short white setae and macrosetae. Scutellum with 2–4 white apical macrosetae. Pleuron silvery tomentose without setae. Wings brownish. Legs reddish yellow with white setae and macrosetae. Femora with black stripe dorsally. Tergites black, with white stripe posteriorly. Hypopygium black with white setae (
<bibRefCitation author="Richter, V. A." box="[1171,1323,1543,1570]" pageId="2" pageNumber="579" refId="ref10985" refString="Richter, V. A. (1968) Robber flies (Diptera, Asilidae) of Caucasus. In: Bychovskiy, B. E. (Eds.), Key to the fauna of the USSR published by the Zoological Institute of AS USSR. Vol. 97. Nauka, Leningrad, pp. 1 - 285. [in Russian]" type="book" year="1968">Richter 1968</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
